---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Biography"
  description="Biographical data for Herman Zvi Freiman compiled from Arolsen Archives, Yad Vashem, and personal records."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Biography</h1>
    <p>Consolidated biographical data compiled from Arolsen Archives (ITS), Yad Vashem records, and personal family documents.</p>

    <!-- Portrait + identification table side by side -->
    <div class="bio-header">
      <figure class="bio-portrait">
        <img
          src="/photos/personal_Zvi_Fraiman_With_Suite_Age_40_Approx.png"
          alt="Herman Zvi Freiman, circa age 40"
        />
        <figcaption>Herman (Zvi) Freiman — portrait, circa age 40. Likely taken in Kfar Ata in the 1950s.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="bio-keyinfo">
        <div class="bio-section-label">Personal Identification</div>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Full Name</td><td>Herman FREIMAN (also: FRAJMAN, FREIMANN)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Hebrew Name</td><td>צבי (Zvi)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Birth Date</td><td>March 2, 1910 (some documents show 1905)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Birthplace</td><td>Boryslaw, Galicia, Poland (now Ukraine)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Religion</td><td>Jewish (Jude)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Profession</td><td>Schneider (Tailor)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Languages</td><td>Polish, Yiddish, Russian, Sign Language</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Nationality</td><td>Polish (polnisch), later Israeli</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="bio-pull">
      Herman Zvi Freiman was born in Boryslaw in 1910.<br />
      His wife and children did not survive the Holocaust. He did.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Parents</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Relation</th><th>Name</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Father</td><td>Feibel FREIMAN (variants: Faivel, Faifel, Fajwel)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mother</td><td>Shifra ROSEN (variants: Schifra, Szyfra) — née Rosen</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Marriage &amp; Family</h2>

    <h3>First Marriage (Pre-War)</h3>
    <p>Herman had a wife and children before WWII who perished during the Holocaust. No documentary records of their names have been found. The 1959 ITS form lists his marital status "at the time of incarceration" as <em>ledig</em> (single), which may have been an administrative simplification or error — family oral history confirms the pre-war family.</p>

    <h3>Second Marriage</h3>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Information</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Wife</td><td>Ester FREIMAN (née unknown)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wife's Birth Date</td><td>April 15, 1920</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Marriage Date</td><td>1945</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Marriage Place</td><td>Poland</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Children</td><td>Three sons (visible in family photograph, names not in documents)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Document Sources</h2>

    <h3>Arolsen Archives (ITS)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>TD (Tracing Document) File 790 495</li>
      <li>DP-2 Cards: September 4, 1946 / November 20, 1946 / July 1, 1947</li>
      <li>DP-3 Card: Assembly Center Registration</li>
      <li>Certificate of Residence No. 413381 (February 26, 1960)</li>
      <li>Power of Attorney (Vollmacht) dated October 20, 1959</li>
      <li>Polish Jewish Registry (Warsaw, January 1947)</li>
      <li>Palestine Emigration Lists (September 30, 1948)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Yad Vashem</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Pinkas HaKehillot (Encyclopedia of Jewish Communities) — Boryslaw entry</li>
      <li>ITS Database Search Results</li>
      <li>Hebrew documentation explaining TD card significance</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Personal Family Archives</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Portrait photograph of Tzvi Freiman in suit (circa age 40)</li>
      <li>Earlier formal portrait photograph</li>
      <li>Family photograph with Ester and three sons in Israel</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .bio-header {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 210px 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .bio-header { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .bio-portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 2px;
    filter: sepia(12%) contrast(97%);
  }
  .bio-portrait figcaption {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-mid-gray);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .bio-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  /* Remove top margin from table immediately following bio-section-label */
  .bio-keyinfo table {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .bio-pull {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
</style>
